webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) Portrait of the Instrumentmaker and Piano Barrier Johan Otto Baumgardt. Born in Stockholm in 1842, he moved to Lköpping in 1864. In the new hometown, he established himself as a manufacturer in St Kors block 59. In 1877, he married Christina Elisabet Nestor, born in Slaka sn in 1838. The spouses died in Lköpping in 1912 and 1914. The couple’s surviving sons Nils and Jonas pushed the company further - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMEA0001240039. (en) Bergh, Peter Johansson. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021017436717. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
